- No, it was badass.

53:50.858 --> 53:54.153
- I'm out.
- What?

53:54.237 --> 53:56.072
I don't wanna be involved.

53:58.657 --> 53:59.908
With what, the business?

53:59.993 --> 54:02.411
With any of it.

54:02.495 --> 54:04.705
What you did to Flaca was weird, Piper.

54:04.788 --> 54:08.042
She's poor.
A lot of these girls, they're poor.

54:08.126 --> 54:10.544
Of course they were excited about money.

54:10.628 --> 54:12.796
They're excited about
a dollar-an-hour job.

54:12.880 --> 54:16.092
- Okay.
- I don't like this version of you.

54:16.175 --> 54:18.469
Well, maybe I don't like
this version of you.

54:19.720 --> 54:21.514
[scoffs] What version is that?

54:21.597 --> 54:25.309
The paranoid, needy version.
The judge-y version.

54:26.269 --> 54:29.230
I mean, fuck, Alex,
what is your problem?

54:30.356 --> 54:33.484
You have no idea what you're getting into.

54:33.567 --> 54:36.904
You don't know who these people are,
you don't know who they're connected to,

54:36.987 --> 54:39.115
and you're on
some weird little power trip.

54:39.198 --> 54:44.453
I am doing exactly what you did,
and you cannot handle it

54:44.537 --> 54:47.123
because you're afraid
I might be better at it than you are.

54:47.206 --> 54:48.457
[scoffs]

54:51.669 --> 54:52.961
[inhales deeply]

54:53.046 --> 54:55.173
You probably are better at it now.

54:56.715 --> 54:58.634
You're a natural.

55:00.553 --> 55:02.012
I'm out, Pipes.

55:03.013 --> 55:06.392
I'm out of that and...

55:06.475 --> 55:08.061
I'm out of this.

55:12.690 --> 55:17.611
So, who's gonna rep us?
We need to elect a leader.

55:17.695 --> 55:19.655
Well, I'd do it, but somebody
needs to explain to me

55:19.738 --> 55:21.824
how the whole thing works.

55:23.451 --> 55:26.454
Holy shit, he's come around.

55:26.537 --> 55:29.123
Dude!
Now it's official.

55:29.832 --> 55:31.125
[sighs]

55:32.793 --> 55:34.128
What are you guys doing?

55:36.004 --> 55:39.175
Do you really wanna make
an enemy out of MCC?

55:40.176 --> 55:42.761
You guys got yourself all riled up

55:42.845 --> 55:46.182
without really considering
what it is you're doing.

55:46.265 --> 55:47.891
We're re-unionizing.

55:47.975 --> 55:49.977
- And it feels so good.
- [Ford] Mmm-hmm.

55:50.060 --> 55:51.104
Right.

55:52.020 --> 55:53.939
What are your exact grievances?

55:54.648 --> 55:56.275
Hmm?

55:56.359 --> 55:59.903
Have you rallied at least
30% support from the employee base?

56:02.198 --> 56:04.825
Have you gotten them all
to sign authorization cards?

56:05.951 --> 56:08.662
How do you guys expect
to be taken seriously?

56:08.746 --> 56:12.291
Shit... you do know
what you're talking about.

56:13.126 --> 56:14.335
You should lead us.

56:14.418 --> 56:16.587
- That's a conflict of interest.
- Uh-uh.

56:16.670 --> 56:18.922
These corporate types
are a different breed.

56:19.006 --> 56:22.426
They're hurting us.
They're hurting our families.

56:22.510 --> 56:23.802
We need a leader.

56:25.221 --> 56:26.514
We need you, man.

56:26.597 --> 56:29.308
We do.
We need you.

56:36.607 --> 56:39.360
Well, for starters,
stop meeting in the break room.

56:39.443 --> 56:42.321
Don't give them
a reason to squash you.

56:42.405 --> 56:44.282
These guys are pros.

56:45.533 --> 56:47.160
They will call a meeting.

56:47.243 --> 56:49.495
It will seem optional,
but it won't be.

56:49.578 --> 56:51.580
And once they have you captive,

56:51.664 --> 56:53.707
they are going to feed you
a bunch of BS

56:53.791 --> 56:56.043
about it being a friendly workplace.

56:56.126 --> 57:00.047
And then they are
going to use scare tactics

57:00.130 --> 57:04.885
to try and convince you
that you're all gonna lose your jobs.

57:05.761 --> 57:07.430
Don't fucking listen to 'em.

57:07.513 --> 57:10.098
They need you
more than you need them.

57:13.977 --> 57:15.146
So, you in?

57:22.653 --> 57:23.696
I could be your guy.

57:23.779 --> 57:25.531
[all cheering]

57:28.617 --> 57:30.161
I don't know about y'all,

57:30.244 --> 57:32.538
but I feel a "Hip, hip, hooray"
coming on right about now.

57:32.621 --> 57:34.290
- Please don't. Please don't.
- Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

57:34.373 --> 57:35.458
- No, it's coming.
- Oh, yeah!

57:35.541 --> 57:37.293
- Hip, hip!
- [all] Hooray!

57:37.376 --> 57:39.002
- Hip, hip!
- [all] Hooray!

57:39.086 --> 57:41.464
- Hip, hip!
- [all] Hooray!

57:41.547 --> 57:42.715
[all cheering]

57:42.798 --> 57:46.302
[O'Neill singing]
♪ Do you hear the people sing ♪

57:46.385 --> 57:49.096
♪ Singing the songs of angry men? ♪

57:49.180 --> 57:55.478
♪ It is the music of the people
who will not be slaves again ♪

57:55.561 --> 57:58.814
♪ When the beating of your heart ♪

57:58.897 --> 58:01.942
♪ Echoes the beating of the drums ♪

58:02.025 --> 58:06.405
♪ There is a life about to start
when tomorrow comes ♪

58:06.489 --> 58:08.031
Black people don't know this song.

